description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen to join the Women and Children administrative team to work as the Colposcopy Co-ordinator supporting the Colposcopy Service. We are looking for a keen, enthusiastic person to provide administrative assistance and secretarial support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an interesting and varied post involving patient contact over the telephone. The successful applicant will be responsible for participating in the coordination of the various aspects of a busy Colposcopy Service, including the co-ordination and organization of outpatient clinics, typing of medical correspondence and dealing with patient and colleagues queries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will have proven strengths in organization and communication and an eye for detail whilst always seeing to ensure the patient is getting the best possible care at RCHT. They will be confident and able to prioritize their workload effectively. Working as part of a friendly, busy team whilst ensuring that the Colposcopy Service meet targets and deadlines. A medical secretarial background within the NHS would be advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent computer and typing skills are essential and knowledge of the PAS system would be desirable but not essential as full training will be given to the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time post working 37.5 hours per week, Monday to Friday, excluding bank holidays. Previous experience in a healthcare setting would be an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nadia Francis, Obs &amp; Gynae Team Co-ordinator: 07826916530. Email: nadia.francis4@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
